Doc,<br><br>
Thanks.  I understand.  I just wondered and now I know a lot more of why you are here.  We all burn out and carry too much baggage.  I wonder sometimes how safe this site is since we all feel so deeply.  Small misjudged comments allows insentivity to seep in and the wall goes back up.  Triggers as Art puts it so well.  We all have them.<br><br>
I respect your honest answer on your need to place yourself in a position where someone else should listen and try to understand.  Something you have done all your life.  If you don't have PTSD from what you have already given, I can't imagine why.  Clinical separation isn't always the answer.  Especially if it is forced on you by event, take my word for that.<br><br>
We all need to stand on the edge of reality and let it hang out.  A cleansing so to speak without fear of overwhelming reprisal.  Shall we call it scream therapy for lack of a better word.<br><br>
If we trust each other with our thoughts that trust should be sacred.  We can disagree on actions, but our reasons that create that disagreement are part of us.<br><br>
Doc,when you are willing to share as you have, I am willing to listen.  A courtesy I give to any honest man.<br><br>
SW
